column5: Stevie how is that move working out for you? Developed a taste for Iron City or Rolling Rock yet?
No way...I am a National Bohemian guy!!!  Things are going along fine out here man, thanks for asking.  You up and att'em again?

LOL Bud just haven`t been out to the barn to check and see if your still on the boat floor. Steve, just haven`t noticed you posting. LOL American life style is a lot more hectic than the laid back Canadians can handle?  Up and att`em? what is that? FF my place is on my azz. Beer wings damn! At least I am not an elitist! Mini Cooper under control? Out

I have been strangely busy with this job stuff...It doesn't leave a lot of spare time.  Spare time then goes to the smallest members of the family, they really don't leave a lot of time.  The wee Coop is doing great, his younger bro Carson (who is now 1 1/2) is doing well and they have another brother (or sister) on the way coming sometime in April.  Tiller!!!
You figured out yet how this keeps happening Steve???
This one is being blamed on Patron Margaritas.
Great to hear from you and that all is well, Steve.
Dang buddy! you have been busy! Glad you are doing well!

Busy is for sure, Mr. Dillon.  Doogle, how goes snocket reintistry?  Still managing more than participating?  It is a gorgeous crisp day here in southern PA.  Sun is out, it is -3 canuckian and me thinks the boys and I will be out cleaning up the leaves and such.  Catch you all later!
